[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring JUnit features**\n\nI’m considering whether the JUnit Platform with Vintage can scan all test classes and run JUnit3 TestCase classes, including any nested ones. It seems intriguing that it might be able to discover public static nested classes as tests. I want to clarify how this scanning process works and if it indeed supports these nested test classes. There’s a lot to unpack here regarding the capabilities of JUnit.\n\n**Considering method imports**\n\nI’m thinking about method names like `createTestCase`. There's a potential conflict with the annotation `junit.framework.Test`. If the code style is to always import classes, I could use `import junit.framework.Test;` and avoid importing `org.junit.jupiter.api.Test` while annotating with `@org.junit.jupiter.api.Test`. Hmm, I wonder if checkstyle would prohibit fully qualified class names? I should probably search style guidelines to confirm.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_037c3dc5b8fa3c72016a24fdc83d4c819392456c0e609d1764\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJP3d5dRiZNc0HXTUDlQNKaVretM0aKe0RrwZ2IvkxRBhf-YxTZmsQLsAFwa0xDCNj1q92ZVVlnAC8QYm3h9d-CwLLgNQE9ZhhyIx8KBqvB1lk2lCnKJ7Z5Yvvx4iL5ZinYdTeW95_wRPALdxX9YUcUUgmLGo2uINjtw_Z82JufaT7qTkBZweIuzoMYxLzLmLde_agRs4jdWhg7hOk457a8zEdqAQt9c3BUHjbJ2QEgCHFyUSVPoZJybCrSv1yiQWyirOmx5cbDn46yNqrmAS306ILVJTeaBLVHm9hRhhIr9NiORXgErRtXrp0-D21T4LsHfwr8cW-xfApSV7xP6_QQHxxDOOibmOxxbzGWmtn0PKD9CHCnXvfQRJXsFxC6HPrkDVAaFJyEtenxcKrUtt2jspcWjZ5XFV2JeAIxwgDqyzr8-_IHRFutJpS7Es0YkGONgfqWRC2fPAzAgRFFVe8X5rPilvyJa9Re1FYE5uf8fkIC0mQ5Uulsr4SeL8iNC6682yMVIhdZRsx9-Y7-LVdSK1GgnnZosT0Ybz83VpHEoasuNQIYtlwwvz1UD_ieRIcv-9F0hObnMqq9uJR1gwHlpfm8S5qVf-9fs6YOe3BR-lClr3bO1AfkCYaoSyJnHdsBdjIQQosZriVqjzppI6QeVGUIdWuLF5SyPrj80-jYu36FqcbL_jTuFnX11p5xuWEExLw208pN6WD85azj4i8Lz9wFG0NnrcX-QpfSOV2wlkdP5mgRi7DRuTa_p1slsjJpwb7S2vi91KnfjB5hH4FS_-iAO_0XbKyzhTww1aK63